  {\pard\sb400\sa200\keepn\f0\fs40\b 1. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW\b0\par}

  {\pard\sb200\sa100\f0\fs28\b 1.1 Stack Summary\b0\par}
  {\pard\sa100\f0\fs24 MattrMindrScribe is a full-stack legal transcript management application:\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b Frontend:\b0  React 18 + TypeScript + Vite 5 + Tailwind CSS 3.4\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b Backend:\b0  Express.js v5 + TypeScript (compiled with tsx at runtime)\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b Database:\b0  PostgreSQL (local instance)\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b Cloud Storage:\b0  Amazon S3 (us-east-2) via @aws-sdk/client-s3 v3\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b AI Services:\b0  OpenAI Whisper (speech-to-text), AssemblyAI (speaker diarization), Anthropic Claude Opus 4 (speaker refinement)\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b Authentication:\b0  JWT (jsonwebtoken + bcryptjs)\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b Process Manager:\b0  PM2 (production)\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b Reverse Proxy:\b0  Nginx (production)\par}

  {\pard\sb200\sa100\f0\fs28\b 1.2 Development Mode\b0\par}
  {\pard\sa100\f0\fs24 In development, two servers run simultaneously via start.sh:\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b Express backend\b0  on port 3000 (started with \f1 npx tsx server/index.ts\f0 )\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f0\fs24 \bullet  \b Vite dev server\b0  on port 5000 (started with \f1 npx vite\f0 )\par}
  {\pard\sa100\f0\fs24 Vite proxies /api and /uploads requests to the Express backend. The start.sh script polls http://localhost:3000/api/health until the backend is ready (up to 30 seconds), then starts Vite. A trap ensures both PIDs are killed on exit.\par}

  {\pard\sb200\sa100\f0\fs28\b 1.3 Production Mode\b0\par}
  {\pard\sa100\f0\fs24 In production (detected by process.env.REPLIT_DEPLOYMENT === '1'), Express runs on port 5000 and serves the pre-built dist/ folder directly. A splat route (/{*splat}) catches all non-API requests and serves index.html for client-side routing. There is no separate Vite process.\par}

  {\pard\sb200\sa100\f0\fs28\b 1.4 Vite Configuration (vite.config.ts)\b0\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f1\fs20 import \{ defineConfig \} from 'vite'\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f1\fs20 import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f1\fs20 export default defineConfig(\{\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f1\fs20   plugins: [react()],\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f1\fs20   server: \{\par}
  {\pard\li720\sa60\f1\fs20     host: '0.0.0.0',\par}
  {\pard\li720\sa60\f1\fs20     port: 5000,\par}
  {\pard\li720\sa60\f1\fs20     allowedHosts: true,\par}
  {\pard\li720\sa60\f1\fs20     proxy: \{\par}
  {\pard\li1080\sa60\f1\fs20       '/api': \{ target: 'http://localhost:3000', changeOrigin: true, timeout: 30 * 60 * 1000 \},\par}
  {\pard\li1080\sa60\f1\fs20       '/uploads': \{ target: 'http://localhost:3000', changeOrigin: true \}\par}
  {\pard\li720\sa60\f1\fs20     \}\par}
  {\pard\li360\sa60\f1\fs20   \}\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f1\fs20 \})\par}

  {\pard\sb200\sa100\f0\fs28\b 1.5 TypeScript Configuration\b0\par}
  {\pard\sa100\f0\fs24 The tsconfig.json targets ES2020, uses bundler module resolution, react-jsx transform, and strict mode. It only includes the src/ directory (frontend). The backend runs via tsx which handles TypeScript compilation at runtime without a separate tsconfig.\par}

  {\pard\sb200\sa100\f0\fs28\b 1.6 Middleware Chain Order (server/index.ts)\b0\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f0\fs24 1. CORS (origin: true, credentials: true)\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f0\fs24 2. Static index.html handler (production only)\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f0\fs24 3. express.json (50MB limit) + express.urlencoded (extended: true)\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f0\fs24 4. Static /uploads directory (protected by authenticateToken)\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f0\fs24 5. API routes (/api/auth, /api/transcripts, /api/folders, /api/mattrmindr, /api/external, /api/media, /api/health)\par}
  {\pard\sa60\f0\fs24 6. express.static(dist) + SPA fallback (production only)\par}
  {\pard\sa100\f0\fs24 Server and request timeouts are set to 30 minutes to accommodate long-running AI transcription pipelines.\par}

  
  {\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\par}

