  {\pard\sb200\sa100\f0\fs28\b 3.9 Inline Migration System\b0\par}
  {\pard\sa100\f0\fs24 All schema migrations run inline in server/index.ts on every server boot. Each migration is wrapped in pool.query().catch() to ignore "already exists" errors, making them fully idempotent. This approach avoids a separate migration tool. Migrations include: adding columns (expected_speakers, pipeline_log, recording_type, practice_area, sub_type, mattrmindr_case_id, mattrmindr_case_name, change_description), creating tables (transcript_summaries, mattrmindr_connections, _migrations), and creating indexes. Data migrations (deduplication) use the _migrations table to run only once.\par}

  
